   <body>
      <context>
         <hazardstatement type="danger">
            <messagepanel>
               <typeofhazard>hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid>
                  <sl>
                     <sli>Electrical equipment must be installed, operated, serviced, and
maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli>Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and follow
safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli>Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided by others,
be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnect device marked
for its function.</sli>
                     <sli>Turn off the upstream disconnection devices.</sli>
                     <sli>Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before working on
or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli>Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous voltage
between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous voltage
can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are
OFF and that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes
before opening the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli>The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to a high leakage
current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note>This procedure shows the 40
kVA UPS but the procedure is identical for all 10-40 kVA UPS systems.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the screws of the front cover and remove the front
cover.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removefrontcover_w120mm_0000166133.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the cover in front of the leftmost fan.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removeinnercover_w120mm_0000166132.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Check that the connectors on the fan speed monitoring board
with the black and red wires are correctly labeled and disconnect
them.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the two screws from the fan speed monitoring board.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removemonitoringboard_w120mm_0000166131.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the two hex nuts on the fan assembly bracket and
remove the fan assembly bracket.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removefanbracket_w120mm_0000166130.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Slide the leftmost fan out and remove it as far as the
wires allow.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removeleftmostfan_w120mm_0000166129.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Move the other fans to the left and slide them out one
by one as far as the wires allow.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removelast3fans_w120mm_0000166128.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>From the new fan box, remove the fan speed monitoring board
and all four fans by sliding them out of the sheet metal frame. Discard
the sheet metal frame.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_removefansandboardsfromnew_w120mm_0000166127.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Replace the old fans with the new fans one by one:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Disconnect the wires from the old fan.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Reconnect the wires to the new fan.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Slide the new fan into position in the fan holder.</p>
                  <stepxmp>
                     <fig>
                        <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_installnewfans_w120mm_0000166126.png"
                               placement="inline"/>
                     </fig>
                  </stepxmp>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the fan assembly bracket with the two hex nuts.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_reinstallfanbracket_w120mm_0000166125.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Replace the old fan speed monitoring board with the new
fan speed monitoring board:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Check that all the DIP switches on the new fan speed
monitoring board are set identically to the old fan speed monitoring
board.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Reconnect the connectors with the black and red wires
to the fan speed monitoring board.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Install the new fan speed monitoring board with the
two screws.</p>
                  <stepxmp>
                     <fig>
                        <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_installnewmonitoringboard_w120mm_0000166124.png"
                               placement="inline"/>
                     </fig>
                  </stepxmp>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the cover in front of the leftmost fan.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/40_kva_replace0j-0n-96453_re-installinnercover_w120mm_0000166143.png"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the front cover with the screws.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <div>Check the proper function of the fan assembly by closing
the Q001 breaker. Only the green LEDs on the fan speed monitoring
board must be on.</div>
   </body>
